(2539, 1, '2015-12-19 07:49:53', '2015-12-19 07:49:53', '[vc_row section_content_width="container-fullwidth" css=".vc_custom_1508675538539{margin-top: -100px !important;}"][vc_column][tt_biography education_label="" career_label="" leader_photo="4051" party_leader_name="NAGARAJA R. RAO, DTM" leader_designation="Executive Director at Bayar\'s Ganesh Food Products &amp; Candidate for second Vice Precident " bio_details="\r\n" bio_info="%5B%7B%7D%5D" social_icon="%5B%7B%7D%5D" education_info="%5B%7B%7D%5D" career_info="%5B%7B%7D%5D"]Nagaraja Rao is a true Toastmaster at heart and carries the fervor of Toastmasters wherever he goes. He has applied the lessons he learnt in Toastmasters in his business and has achieved remarkable success. Nagaraja has coached several individuals to become champion speakers and great leaders. His ability to generate simple solutions to complex issues, along with his pleasant nature, makes him an excellent mentor.\r\n\r\nHis love for coffee and a penchant for entrepreneurship have blended perfectly to create business success. Nagaraja is the executive director of Ganesh Food Products (Pvt) Ltd., which owns the brand BayarÂ´s Coffee. His company also has exclusive manufacturing arrangements with major brands such as:\r\n\r\n<img style="width: 100%;" src="../../wp-content/uploads/2015/12/naga_333.png" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAs an entrepreneur, Nagaraja is a part of the United Coffee Association of India; the Indian Coffee Trade Association, and the Federation of Karnataka Chambers of Commerce and Industry.\r\n\r\nHe enjoys playing sports, and is an active member of the Karnataka State Rifle Association, India.\r\n\r\nHe believes that an integral part of being a leader is giving back to society. He does community service and is part of Shivalli Smartha Brahmana Mahaparishath.\r\n\r\nNagaraja loves travelling around the world and makes it a point to visit one of the local Toastmasters club whenever possible. He understands that being a leader is a responsibility that involves making a difference. Thus his theme:Â <span class="highlight">BE THE DIFFERENCE, THAT MAKES A DIFFERENCE.</span>[/tt_biography][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1452793090788{padding-bottom: 112px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_row_inner equal_height="yes" content_placement="middle" css=".vc_custom_1452022137160{margin: 0px !important;}"][vc_column_inner css=".vc_custom_1452104240428{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-right: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}" offset="vc_col-md-6"][vc_single_image image="3951" img_size="full" alignment="center" css=".vc_custom_1508677760346{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner css=".vc_custom_1508678074935{padding-top: 50px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 50px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;background-color: #222222 !important;}" offset="vc_col-md-6"][vc_column_text el_class="white-text"]\r\n<h3>Popularity</h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class="white-text"]\r\n<div id="why" class="container-fluid">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="checks">\r\n\r\nNagaraja is defined by his passion for Servant Leadership. He firmly believes in the Toastmasters tagline Where Leaders Are Made. He has seen how Toastmasters has transformed him into a leader in his business and community. He is now keen to enable others to use this program to make a difference to themselves and others. He is eager to demonstrate his belief that we all canÂ <span class="highlight">\'BE THE DIFFERENCE, THAT MAKES A DIFFERENCE\'.</span>\r\n\r\nAs a board member he will bring his 12 years of Toastmaster experience and his 25 years as a businessman to bear on such issues as policymaking, team-building, dedication, problem-solving, financial oversight, planning, marketing, delegation, and goal-setting. His cumulative knowledge from living and working in such a diverse area of the world will help him serve Toastmasters well as our organization expands in an ever changing world.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="achievements" class="container-fluid"></div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1508675942140{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 6px !important;padding-bottom: 120px !important;}"][vc_column][tt_section_title title_alignment="text-center" section_separator="no" title="career - history"]Practicing the art and science of coffee manufacturing since 1993\r\nWalking on the path of Servant Leadership since 2002\r\n\r\nSpecialties: Certified Coffee Taster, with broad experience in all aspects of manufacture and marketing of Roast &amp;Ground Filter Coffee and Espresso blends. Clients include Costa Coffee, Dunkin Donuts, Au Bon Pain, Krispy Kreme, Mad over Donuts, Chocolate Room, Bru World Cafe\r\n\r\nToastmasters International:\r\nRegion Advisor (India, Sri Lanka, China, Taiwan, Japan and Korea)(2013-14)\r\nRegion 13 was the Best performing region in the world[/tt_section_title][tt_stories][tt_story story_lists="3826" word_limit="10" link_visibility="visible" story_year="2010" title="Creating the party\'s brand" link="url:%23||"][tt_story story_lists="3861" word_limit="10" content_positon="timeline-inverted" link_visibility="visible" story_year="2011" title="Registering political party" link="url:%23||"][tt_story story_lists="2392" word_limit="10" link_visibility="visible" story_year="2012" title="Making a better manifesto" link="url:%23||"][tt_story story_lists="3721" word_limit="10" content_positon="timeline-inverted" link_visibility="visible" story_year="2013" title="Joining Electoral Commission" link="url:%23||"][tt_story story_lists="3686" word_limit="10" link_visibility="visible" story_year="2014" title="Leading the party" link="url:%23||"][/tt_stories][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about', '', '', '2017-10-22 14:41:35', '2017-10-22 14:41:35', ''