r_option="custom-color" title="About-Nagaraja Rao"][/tt_section_title][/vc_column][vc_column offset="vc_col-lg-5 vc_col-md-6" el_class="aboutng"][vc_single_image image="4256" img_size="full" css=".vc_custom_1510749995297{background-image: url() !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column el_class="home_intro1" offset="vc_col-lg-7 vc_col-md-6"][tt_section_title title_alignment="text-center" section_separator="no" el_class="text_e"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">NAGARAJAÂ  RAO, DTM</h2>\r\n<h3>Executive Director at Bayar\'s Ganesh Food Products &amp; Candidate for Second Vice President.</h3>\r\nNagaraja is an ardent coffee connoisseur and has a passion for leadership, which has led him to excel in his profession, in Toastmasters and in a number of volunteer positions. The business he co-founded in 1988 has grown into a major coffee producing company serving cafÃ© chains such as Aromas Coffee, Costa Coffee, Dunkin Donuts, Krispy Kreme Doughnuts, Di Bella Coffee, Au Bon Pain, The Chocolate Room and Mc CafÃ©.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHe is also a member and a voluntary leader in the United Coffee Association of India, the Indian Coffee Trade Association, and the Federation of Karnataka Chambers of Commerce and Industry.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHe believes that the quality of <strong>leaders</strong>Â is reflected in the standards they set for themselves and the way in which they give back to society. Â As a Trustee of Amruthur Education Trust, he helps provide quality education to rural children. As an active member of Shivalli Smartha Brahmana Mahaparishath, he helps provide scholarships and job opportunities for weaker sections of society.[/tt_section_title][/vc_column][vc_column el_class="home_intro1 home_intro2"][tt_section_title title_alignment="text-center" section_separator="no" el_class="text_e"]Being a man of few words, he tends to listen more, seek to understand others and introspect to find solutions. It helps him to keep an open mind, make informed decisions and work collaboratively. He likes to focus on doing small things that make a big difference. Being practical and value driven, he believes it is better to let actions speak louder than words.[/tt_section_title][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1508955411165{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}" el_id="home_intro2_img"][vc_column width="1/2" el_class="home_intro2"][tt_section_title title_alignment="text-center" title_color_option="custom-color" section_separator="no" el_class="text_e text_black" title="work - experience" title_color="#000000"]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Nagaraja Rao is a true Toastmaster at heart and carries the fervor of Toastmasters wherever he goes. He has applied the lessons he learnt in Toastmasters in his business and has achieved remarkable success. Nagaraja has coached several individuals to become champion speakers and great leaders. His ability to generate simple solutions to complex issues, along with his pleasant nature, makes him an excellent mentor.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">His love for coffee and a penchant for entrepreneurship have blended perfectly to create business success. Nagaraja is the executive director of Ganesh Food Products (Pvt) Ltd., which owns the brand BayarÂ´s Coffee</p>\r\n[/tt_section_title][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="4266" img_size="full" el_class="AboutImg"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1512493168651{margin-top: -100px !important;}" el_id="why_naga"][vc_column offset="vc_col-xs-12"][tt_section_title title_alignment="text-center" title_color_option="custom-color" section_separator="no" title="Why - Nagaraja Rao" css=".vc_custom_1513784948723{padding-top: 20px !important;}"][/tt_section_title][tt_biography education_label="" career_label="" leader_photo="4331" party_leader_name="NAGARAJA RAO, DTM" leader_designation="Candidate for Second Vice President " bio_details="\r\n" bio_info="%5B%7B%7D%5D" social_icon="%5B%7B%7D%5D" education_info="%5B%7B%7D%5D" career_info="%5B%7B%7D%5D" el_class="why_naga"]\r\n<div class="row r1">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">\r\n\r\nâ€œBe the Difference that makes a Differenceâ€ is not just my campaign theme, but a guiding principle. I believe that even our smallest actions can have a positive impact in someoneâ€™s life. We are all capable of making a difference, and we must do what we can.\r\n\r\nAs District 82 Governor in 2010-11, I led one of the most diverse districts in the world. India has a population of 1.3 billion people, with 22 official languages and more than 2000 dialects. Sri Lanka has a population of 21 million. Managing such diversity was a huge challenge. My Toastmaster teams came up with exceptional trainings, contests and conferences. District 82 ended up being the number one district in the world, both when I was the Lt. Governor of Education &amp; Training and the District Governor.\r\n\r\nAs Region 13 Advisor I worked with leaders from China, Taiwan, Japan, India, Sri Lanka and South Korea, which made me appreciate even more diversity and the power of Toastmasters to bring people together.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/tt_biography][/vc_column][vc_column el_class="colwhy" offset="vc_col-lg-12 vc_col-md-12 vc_col-xs-12"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">\r\n\r\nAs an International Director, I gained a better understanding of the Board dynamics and effectiveness. It made me embrace the culture of constructive challenges and healthy debates, collective decision making and speaking with one voice.\r\n\r\nI am keen to â€˜make a differenceâ€™ as Second Vice President. With 30 years of international business experience and 15 years in Toastmasters leadership, I believe I can contribute immensely in strategic planning, developing policies and financial oversight. I am eager to work with the Board to make Toastmasters even more successful.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-10 col-sm-4 col-xs-3"><a style="color: black;" href="http://www.toastmasters.org/about/board-of-directors/International%20Officer%20Candidates/%7BB8E0EEFB-4C74-4A16-BE24-6E7E6951A703%7D" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><button class="btn" type="button"><strong>Biography</strong></button></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="row achievementrow" style="padding-left: 90px;">\r\n<div class="col-lg-1 col-xs-2 col" style="margin-right: 40px;"><img class="imgs" style="width: 100px; height: auto;" src="http://nagarajafor2ndvp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/logo4-150x150.jpg" alt="Nagaraja" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-1 col-xs-2 col" style="margin-right: 40px;"><img class="imgs" style="width: 100px; height: auto;" src="http://nagarajafor2ndvp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/logo6-150x150.jpg" alt="Nagaraja" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-1 col-xs-2 col" style="margin-right: 40px;"><img class="imgs" style="width: 100px; height: auto;" src="http://nagarajafor2ndvp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/logo5-150x150.jpg" alt="Nagaraja" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-1 col-xs-2 col" style="margin-right: 40px;"><img class="imgs" style="width: 100px; height: auto;" src="http://nagarajafor2ndvp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/logo3-150x150.jpg" alt="Nagaraja" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-1 col-xs-2 col" style="margin-right: 40px;"><img class="imgs" style="width: 100px; height: auto;" src="http://nagarajafor2ndvp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/logo2-150x150.jpg" alt="Nagaraja" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-1 col-xs-2 col" style="margin-right: 40px;"><img class="imgs" style="width: 100px; height: auto;" src="http://nagarajafor2ndvp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/logo1-150x150.jpg" alt="Nagaraja" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-lg-1 col-xs-2 col col1" style="margin-right: 40px;"><img class="imgs" style="width: 100px; height: auto;" src="http://nagarajafor2ndvp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/logo8-150x150.jpg" alt="Nag